                    90 cm
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="species-info-box">
                <div class="info-box-header">          
                    台灣棲地分布
                </div>
                <div class="info-box-text">
                    分布台灣全島1000-2500公尺之間。少見。
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="species-info-box">
                <div class="info-box-header">          
                    世界棲地分布
                </div>
                <div class="info-box-text">
                    台灣特有亞種。
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="species-info-box">
                <div class="info-box-header">          
                    外觀描述
                </div>
                <div class="info-box-text" lang="en-US">
                    Small snake; total length up to 90 cm. There are 15-21 (17 at mid-body) rows of keeled scales; anteriorly dorso-lateral scales are oblique. Head is oval, triangular and distinct from neck; body is slightly stout; tail is long. Eye is medium to large size; iris is light flesh-colored with flecks of black, and darkened in lower two-thirds; pupil is round, black, surrounded by narrow ring of light flesh. Tongue is maroon, fork tips may be gray. It has enlarged rear fangs. The color of upper surface is extensively varied among individuals, including grey, green, yellow, orange, brown, and purple. A dark stripe extends from eye to base of jaw, and usually a reddish or black chevron sits on the nape, with its apex pointing toward the head. There are light bands along the vertebral ridge and dark squares on the sides of the bands; a light mid-dorsal stripe runs along the tail. Ventral surface is whitish anteriorly, gradually tinted with pinkish and may be mottled with black or white pigment in following part of body; the black spots aggregating on sides of the ventrals usually form a longitudinal stripe. The ventrals in anterior body may also have scattered quadrangular marks of black pigment which are irregularly arranged on sides. Anal scale is divided and subcaudals are paired. 
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="species-info-box">
                <div class="info-box-header">          
                    生態描述
                </div>
                <div class="info-box-text"> 	
                    <div class="info-box-paragraph">
                        白天與夜晚皆會出沒，此種後溝牙蛇類(<span lang="en-US">rear-fanged=opistoglyphous</span>,請見附註<i>(1)</i>) 喜歡棲息在山林潮濕的地區，尤其是靠近河流或小溪的地方，因為牠們喜歡補食蛙類和山椒魚。此種蛇類為卵生，但只有很少一部分的人了解牠們的繁殖過程。當牠遇敵時，會舉起頭部與頸部，並且膨脹頸部達到威嚇效果。有點類似眼鏡蛇，可是沒有眼鏡蛇膨脹的那麼大。
                    </div>
                    <span lang="en-US">Th</span>此種蛇類體背底色個體間差異性很大，除了一般常見的褐色和灰褐色之外，還有偏紅、偏黃、偏灰、偏綠、偏橘與偏紫等等。
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="species-info-box">
                <div class="info-box-header">          
                    學名與俗名
                </div>
                <div class="info-box-text">
                    <div class="info-box-paragraph">
                        <span lang="en-US"><i>Pseudoxenodon</i></span>: 希臘文; <span lang="en-US"><i>pseudo</i></span> 的意思是"偽裝" ; <span lang="en-US"><i>xenodon</i></span> (意指 "異齒蛇屬") 是一種產自中南美洲的蛇。
                    </div>
                    <div class="info-box-paragraph">
                        <span lang="en-US"><i>stejnegeri</i></span>: 來自 <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" rel="noreferrer" class="site-link" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leonhard_Hess_Stejneger" lang="en-US">Leonhard Hess Stejneger</a>, (1851-1943), 他是一位出生在挪威的爬蟲學家，後來在1881年移居到美國，1889年在史密森學會(<span lang="en-US">Smithsonian Institution</span>)擔任爬蟲館館長。
                    </div>
                    史丹吉氏斜鱗蛇、花尾斜鱗蛇(中國大陸)、紋尾斜鱗蛇 
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="species-info-box">
                <div class="info-box-header">          
                    附註
                </div>
                <div class="info-box-text">
                    (1) "<i><span lang="en-US">Opisthoglyphous snakes</span>(後溝牙蛇 - <span lang="en-US">opistho</span>為後面之意，<span lang="en-US">glyphos</span>則為溝槽) ，有微毒，牠是利用上顎的後方一對擴大的牙齒來注入毒液。 這種毒牙在蛇閉合嘴吧時並不會垂直下降刺穿蛇的嘴，而是有隨著蛇的嘴開合而往後方斜向升降，蛇的嘴中有一對溝槽可以在閉合時收納這對毒牙。一般俗稱"<span lang="en-US">rear-fanged snakes</span>"</i>"。(<a target="_blank" rel="noopener" rel="noreferrer" class="site-link" href="http://www.smarley.nl/main.php/v/Opisthoglyph/" lang="en-US">Source</a>)                
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="species-info-box">
                <div class="info-box-header">          
